wt.util

Class CallRegistrar

  • java.lang.Object
    • wt.util.CallRegistrar

  • public final class CallRegistrar
extends java.lang.Object
    This class allows one body of code to quickly register the entry and exit of significant calls or states and another body of code to easily monitor the number and total duration of such occurrences on both a per thread and per CallRegistrar instance basis.

    A single instance of this class should generally be created and held in a static for an entire category of call statistic. For instance, a single instance is held and exposed by wt.rmi.RMICallRegistrar to enable monitor of all RMI calls and their duration for the whole JVM.

    Supported API: true

    Extendable: false
